---
import { getEntry } from "astro:content";

import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../../components/PageHeader.astro";
import EvidenceCallout from "../../components/EvidenceCallout.astro";
import ReproSteps from "../../components/ReproSteps.astro";

const fakeStoreEntry = await getEntry("caseStudies", "fake-store");

if (!fakeStoreEntry) {
  throw new Error("Missing case study entry: fake-store");
}

const { Content } = await fakeStoreEntry.render();
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Fake Store Case Study"
  description="End-to-end Fake Store analytics case study on Axiomatic Engine."
  enableMermaid={true}
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Case Study"
    title="Fake Store Case Study"
    lede="A reference pipeline demonstrating ingestion policies, transformation orchestration, and reproducible outcomes."
  />

  <section>
    <h2>Problem</h2>
    <p>
      The objective is to turn Fake Store API records into reliable analytics tables with deterministic
      reruns. The case study demonstrates how project-specific logic sits outside engine internals while
      still using a common orchestration contract.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Architecture</h2>
    <p>
      The pipeline follows a medallion flow: bronze ingestion via dlt, silver typed staging models, and
      gold analytical models. Ingestion and transformation are coordinated by the engine, while project
      resources and normalisation stay in project scope.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Data model</h2>
    <p>
      Current documentation confirms analytical modelling intent and medallion layering. As model-level
      artefacts are published, this section will link dimensional structures and grain choices directly
      to dbt model files.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Transform logic</h2>
    <p>
      Transformation follows a dbt-first approach, triggered after ingestion when enabled. The
      <code>run_pipeline.py</code> entrypoint applies CLI-over-env settings and delegates stage execution
      to engine orchestration.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Data quality/tests</h2>
    <p>
      Validation responsibilities are aligned to dbt and pipeline contracts. The project notes include
      idempotent and deterministic rerun expectations, with test and query artefacts to be expanded as
      publication-ready outputs are captured.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Results/insights</h2>
    <p>
      Current evidence demonstrates repeatable load behaviour and clear runtime boundaries. Outcome
      metrics and analytical findings are intentionally held until query result snapshots and visuals are
      added to the public artefact set.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Trade-offs/lessons</h2>
    <p>
      Resource-level load hints improve rerun reliability, but they introduce additional configuration
      decisions per endpoint. The scope is intentionally narrow and transparent, favouring reproducible
      behaviour over broad feature claims.
    </p>
  </section>

  <ReproSteps
    steps={fakeStoreEntry.data.reproducibility.map((item) => item.command)}
    assumptions={fakeStoreEntry.data.assumptions}
    limitations={fakeStoreEntry.data.limitations}
  />

  <EvidenceCallout
    title="Evidence map"
    items={fakeStoreEntry.data.evidence.map((item) => ({
      label: item.claim,
      path: item.sourcePath,
      note: item.status,
      type: item.type
    }))}
  />

  <section>
    <h2>Source Narrative</h2>
    <Content />
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
